    ALP: Fix YAML examples for Ignition + Miscellaneous improvements (#64)
    
    * Make ALP download link clickable
    
    * Link to Ignition project page
    
    * Use $releasever correctly
    
    In repo URLs, $releasever as a literal string (not a shell variable) will get
    substituted by zypper.
    
    See Variable Substitution in man zypper, or
    https://github.com/openSUSE/zypper/blob/5ff5fa8f53c313f9ffb82883b1b761c87444e34c/doc/zypper.8.txt#L996
    
    * Fix YAML syntax in example
    
    One space of misindentation results in very cryptic error messages by Ruby or
    Python YAML parsers.
    
    * The key is filesystems, not filesystem.
    
    * wipe_filesystem doesn't target a partition table
    
    * Fix YAML syntax AND Butane validity.
    
    As this commit shows, it is very easy to produce invalid YAML, by using TABs
    instead of spaces, or misindentation.
    
    Further, even valid YAML can be invalid for Butane. I have checked with the
    `butane` command and with the spec at
    https://github.com/coreos/butane/blob/main/docs/config-fcos-v1_0.md
    
    Here are two small YAML validators. Ruby has cryptic error messages but
    includes YAML in the standard library. Python has better messages, needs a
    library.
    
    ```rb
    require "yaml"
    yaml_s = ARGF.read
    data = YAML.safe_load(yaml_s)
    print YAML.dump(data)
    ```
    
    Required: python3-PyYAML.rpm
    
    ```py
    import yaml
    import sys
    fn = sys.argv[1]
    with open(fn) as f:
        data = yaml.safe_load(f)
    print(data)
    ```
    
    * Make the example code usable for copy-pasting, on Tumbleweed
    
    Co-authored-by: Martin Vidner <mvidner@suse.com>

